0but%20economists%20and%20demographers%20I%20talked%20to%20say%20the%20vast%20majority%20%E2%80%94%20or%20whatever%20is%20left%20of%20it%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-not-enough-retirement-savings-gen-z-millennials-eldercare-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecostly%20retirements%20and%20eldercare%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20will%20end%20up%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20millennials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReed%20was%20right%2C%20though.%20Gen%20X%20really%20is%20the%20forgotten%20generation.%20These%20poor%20middle-agers%2C%20former%20latchkey%20kids%20raised%20on%20MTV%2C%20are%20now%20toiling%20in%20the%20shadows%2C%20upstaged%20by%20the%20splashier%20generations%20on%20either%20side%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20boomers%20kind%20of%20sucked%20up%20all%20the%20air%20in%20the%20room%2C%26quot%3B%20Eric%20Finnigan%2C%20a%20demograher%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjbrec.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohn%20Burns%3C%2Fa%3E%20Research%20and%20Consulting%2C%20tells%20me.%20Millennials%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20get%20all%20this%20attention%20as%20the%20children%20of%20the%20boomers.%20Gen%20X%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20%26quot%3Bhas%20this%20reputation%20as%20kind%20of%20being%20on%20their%20own%2C%26quot%3B%20Finnigan%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Xers%20appear%20to%20be%20doing%20just%20fine%20on%20the%20housing%20front%3A%20They%20were%20the%20highest-earning%20buyers%20last%20year%2C%20and%20around%2070%25%20of%20them%20own%20their%20homes%2C%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%20and%20the%20Census%20Bureau%20shows.%20But%20while%20millennials%20may%20look%20enviously%20at%20their%20ho-hum%20path%20to%20prosperity%2C%20Gen%20Xers%20got%20screwed%20in%20their%20own%20way%2C%20too.%20The%20typical%20Gen%20Xer%20bought%20their%20first%20home%20in%202004%2C%20in%20the%20thick%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-bubble-home-prices-stay-high-crash-real-estate-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehousing%20bubble%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20NAR%20data%20shows.%20After%20the%20financial%20crisis%2C%20their%20cohort%20was%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20end%20up%20underwater%20on%20their%20homes.%20By%202014%2C%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20owed%20more%20on%20their%20mortgages%20than%20their%20houses%20were%20worth%2C%20NAR%20found%2C%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20any%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20Gen%20Xers%20have%20recovered%20financially%20since%20then%2C%20says%20Jessica%20Lautz%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20NAR%20who%20studies%20demographic%20trends.%20Now%2C%20though%2C%20they're%20caught%20in%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20bind%20as%20they%20care%20for%20%3Cem%3Etwo%3C%2Fem%3E%20generations%20with%20vastly%20different%20needs.%20A%20survey%20published%20in%20September%20by%20John%20Burns%20indicated%20that%20around%2040%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20living%20on%20their%20own%20still%20got%20financial%20help%20from%20their%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20probably%20Gen%20Xers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20financial%20pressure%20on%20this%20generation%2C%20actually%2C%26quot%3B%20Lautz%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReed%20knows%20this%20all%20too%20well.%20We%20talked%20on%20the%20phone%20a%20few%20days%20after%20she%20emailed%20me%2C%20and%20I%20was%20struck%20by%20how%20much%20her%20predicament%20speaks%20to%20the%20stress%20of%20being%20a%20Gen%20Xer%20these%20days.%20Her%20parents%20are%20in%20their%2080s%2C%20divorced%2C%20and%20dealing%20with%20various%20health%20issues.%20Each%20of%20them%20is%20a%20homeowner%20for%20now%2C%20but%20Reed%20knows%20that%20in%20the%20not-so-distant%20future%2C%20she'll%20have%20to%20move%20them%20into%20senior%20living.%20Then%20she'll%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20to%20do%20with%20their%20property%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20the%20houses%2C%20but%20the%20decades'%20worth%20of%20stuff%20stashed%20inside.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20just%20beyond%20daunting%2C%26quot%3B%20Reed%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReed%20and%20her%20husband%20also%20send%20money%20each%20month%20to%20their%20two%20children%2C%20ages%2027%20and%2030%2C%20who%20rent%20homes%20in%20California%20and%20Arizona%20because%20they%20can't%20afford%20to%20buy.%20Reed%20says%20she's%20trying%20to%20save%20up%20to%20help%20them%20with%20down%20payments%20when%20they're%20ready.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20work%20full%20time%2C%20my%20husband%20works%20full%20time%2C%20and%20we%20just%20kind%20of%20do%20what%20we%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20Reed%20says.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20balance%20it%2C%20because%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20choice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReed%20says%20between%20the%20monthly%20payments%20to%20her%20children%20and%20all%20those%20trips%20to%20take%20care%20of%20her%20parents%20when%20health%20crises%20strike%20%E2%80%94%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20time%20off%20from%20work%20%E2%80%94%20she%20has%20no%20idea%20how%20much%20all%20of%20this%20is%20costing%20her.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%20Her%20own%20children%2C%20%26quot%3Bcuspers%26quot%3B%20who%20may%20count%20as%20either%20young%20millennials%20or%20older%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20depending%20on%20your%20definition%2C%20are%20already%20begging%20her%20not%20to%20leave%20them%20with%20piles%20of%20stuff%20and%20an%20aging%20property%20that%20requires%20lots%20of%20maintenance.%20Reed's%20goal%2C%20she%20says%2C%20is%20to%20eventually%20sell%20their%20house%20and%20move%20into%20an%20apartment%20out%20west%2C%20closer%20to%20the%20kids.%20She%20hopes%20to%20leave%20them%20with%20money%2C%20not%20a%20bunch%20of%20open-ended%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20financial%20pressures%20have%20other%20Gen%20Xers%20fretting%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-retirement-savings-crisis-401k-kids-parents-work-caregiving-2024-12%5C%22%